---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import RelatedWorkflows from '../../components/RelatedWorkflows.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'Compare', url: '/compare' },
  { name: 'Best Dog Breeding Software', url: '/compare/best-dog-breeding-software' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What is the best puppy waitlist software for dog breeders?',
    answer: 'Puppy waitlist software needs to do three things at once: capture applications from prospective buyers, collect and track deposits, and convert approved applicants into a buyer portal once a puppy is matched. BreederHQ does all three in one system, with deposit tracking, contract signing, and a per-buyer portal built in. BreederBuddy includes a buyer portal but no public marketplace. Breeder Cloud Pro offers a "Find a Breeder" directory but a thinner waitlist workflow. If puppy waitlist plus deposit tracking is the main reason you are buying software, BreederHQ is the most complete option.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does puppy deposit software work in BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'Puppy deposits in BreederHQ are tracked per applicant on the waitlist, tied to a specific litter or program, and settled through Stripe directly into your bank account. You see who paid, when, how much, and against which planned breeding, with refund handling and contract signing in the same workflow. No PayPal screenshots, no spreadsheet reconciliation, no "did I get your deposit?" emails.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is this the ultimate dog breeding software, or just one option?',
    answer: 'For a working program that needs heat tracking, multi-point progesterone timing, litters, waitlists, deposits, contracts, a buyer portal, and a public marketplace presence in one place, BreederHQ is the most complete operational dog breeding software in 2026. It is not the cheapest option, and it is not the right pick for a pedigree-only club registry. The comparison table on this page is the honest version of that trade-off.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the best dog breeding software in 2026?',
    answer: 'There is no single "best" tool, because the right tool depends on what you actually do every day. For a working program that needs heat tracking, progesterone timing, litters, waitlists, deposits, contracts, a buyer portal, and a public listing presence in one system, BreederHQ is the most complete option and offers a 14-day free trial. For dog and cat programs that want a clean records system at a flat price, BreederBuddy at $29.99/mo is a reasonable pick. For multi-species record-keeping at the lowest price, Breeder Cloud Pro starts at $6.99/mo. For a website-plus-pedigree tool with species-aware genetics and a free entry tier, Breed Ledger starts free and rises to $29/mo and $49/mo. Pedigree-driven clubs are better served by ZooEasy, Kintraks, or PedFast. The comparison table below maps the trade-offs.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does BreederHQ compare to BreederBuddy?',
    answer: 'BreederBuddy is dog or cat (one toggle, one species per account) at $29.99/mo or $300/year, with a 30-day free trial and no credit card required to start. BreederHQ is nine species under one account (dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, cattle) with a 14-day free trial. BreederHQ includes a built-in marketplace at marketplace.breederhq.com, OFA Sync that pulls test results automatically from the Orthopedic Foundation for Animals, and a CHIC Readiness Widget for breed-specific health-test planning. BreederBuddy does not publicly offer those. BreederBuddy has a longer free trial and a cleaner, simpler interface if all you want is records-plus-buyers for a single-species dog or cat program.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does BreederHQ compare to Breeder Cloud Pro?',
    answer: 'Breeder Cloud Pro starts at $6.99/mo (Standard) or $13.99/mo (Pro), supports seven species (dog, cat, horse, goat, rabbit, sheep, and "Little Critters"), and offers a 30-day free trial. It publicly claims 17,000+ breeders and 110,000+ animals tracked, and includes a public "Find a Breeder" directory. BreederHQ supports nine species in one account, adds OFA Sync, CHIC Readiness, Volhard PAT and Gun Dog Aptitude temperament testing, and Scout AI document extraction, plus a buyer-facing marketplace at marketplace.breederhq.com. BreederHQ offers a 14-day free trial. Breeder Cloud Pro is the more mature multi-species records-and-pedigree option at a lower entry price; BreederHQ is the more feature-complete operations system with marketplace exposure included.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is BreederHQ really free?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ offers a 14-day free trial of the full platform. The first 100 founding subscribers can also use code FOUNDER50 at checkout for 50% off Pro or Enterprise for 12 months. Verify current pricing on the pricing page.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the difference between dog breeding software and a dog breeding marketplace?',
    answer: 'A marketplace helps buyers find you. Breeding software runs your program: heats, breedings, litters, waitlists, contracts, buyer portal. Most breeders need both. BreederHQ includes both in one system. BreederBuddy, Breeder Cloud Pro, and Dog Breeder Pro do not include a marketplace; you would pair them with a third-party listing site.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Will dog breeding software work for multiple breeds?',
    answer: 'Good operational dog breeding software should. Different breeds have different cycle patterns and different health-testing requirements. BreederHQ handles one breed or many, and applies breed-specific health-testing expectations through its CHIC Readiness Widget.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does dog breeding software calculate COI?',
    answer: 'The good tools do. BreederHQ calculates COI from your pedigree data so you can evaluate a planned breeding before you make it, not after the litter is on the ground.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How is progesterone test timing handled?',
    answer: 'A serious tool lets you log multiple tests across a heat, plot the trend, and surface the optimal breeding window. If the tool only accepts a single date, it is not built for modern dog breeding. BreederHQ supports multi-point progesterone tracking on each heat.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can buyers see their puppy information directly?',
    answer: 'In BreederHQ, yes. Each buyer has a portal with their puppy records, photos, pedigree, contracts, and documents. This is the single biggest time win in modern breeder software.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does it work on the phone?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ is designed mobile-first. The whelping area, the show grounds, and the front porch with a buyer are all places the tool needs to work, not just the desk.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What about AKC and registry support?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ tracks registration numbers, titles, DNA profiles, and the documentation you need for litter registrations. Generated outputs can be used to support registry submissions.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Does OFA and health test data live on the pedigree?',
    answer: 'Yes. Health testing recorded on the dog surfaces on the pedigree so you can see clearances at a glance when planning breedings.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What happens to my data if I leave?',
    answer: 'You can export your data. If a tool traps your data, you do not own your program, you rent it. This applies to every breeding tool, not just BreederHQ.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is BreederHQ built for dogs?',
    answer: 'Yes. Dog breeding is operationally the most complex breeding program to run: narrow breeding windows, progesterone-driven timing, individual puppy records, waitlists, deposits, contracts, and a high-touch buyer experience. BreederHQ is built around those workflows natively. Other species are supported, but the dog program is the center of the product.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Why do you not rank competitors with stars or scores?',
    answer: 'Because a star rating implies we ran a controlled, repeatable evaluation across vendors, and we have not. We describe public positioning honestly and point out where each tool center of gravity is. That is a more useful signal for an operational buyer than a number.'
  }
];

// Workflow stages: visual content only, NOT structured data
const workflowStages = [
  'Heat Cycle',
  'Progesterone',
  'Breeding',
  'Pregnancy',
  'Whelping',
  'Puppy Records',
  'Applications',
  'Deposits',
  'Contracts',
  'Placement'
];

// Article schema: page-level "buyer's guide" intent signal
const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Best Dog Breeding Software 2026: Puppy Waitlist, Deposits & Buyer Portal Compared",
  "description": "An honest, working-breeder comparison of dog breeding software in 2026. BreederHQ vs. BreederBuddy, Breeder Cloud Pro, Dog Breeder Pro, Breedera, ZooEasy, Kintraks, PedFast, and Breed Ledger on heats, progesterone, litters, waitlists, contracts, buyer portals, pricing, and marketplace presence.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "BreederHQ",
    "url": "https://breederhq.com"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "BreederHQ",
    "url": "https://breederhq.com",
    "logo": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "url": "https://breederhq.com/logo.svg"
    }
  },
  "image": "https://breederhq.com/og-image.jpg",
  "datePublished": "2026-05-16",
  "dateModified": "2026-06-26",
  "mainEntityOfPage": {
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "@id": "https://breederhq.com/compare/best-dog-breeding-software"
  }
};

// ItemList schema: compared products only (not workflow stages)
const itemListSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "ItemList",
  "name": "Dog Breeding Software Compared",
  "description": "Operational comparison of dog breeding software products in 2026.",
  "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
  "numberOfItems": 9,
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "BreederHQ" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "BreederBuddy" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Breeder Cloud Pro" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Dog Breeder Pro" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Breedera" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "ZooEasy" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Kintraks" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "PedFast" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Breed Ledger" }
  ]
};

// Page-specific SoftwareApplication schema: BreederHQ is the answer this comparison recommends
// for working dog programs that want operations + marketplace in one system.
const softwareSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
  "name": "BreederHQ",
  "applicationCategory": "BusinessApplication",
  "applicationSubCategory": "Dog Breeding Software",
  "operatingSystem": "Web, iOS, Android",
  "url": "https://breederhq.com",
  "description": "Dog breeding software with heat-cycle tracking, multi-point progesterone timing, individual puppy records, waitlists, deposits, contracts, buyer portal, OFA Sync, CHIC Readiness Widget, COI calculation, Volhard PAT and Gun Dog Aptitude temperament testing, and a built-in public marketplace at marketplace.breederhq.com. Supports nine species in one account: dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, and cattle.",
  "featureList": [
    "Heat cycle tracking",
    "Multi-point progesterone timing",
    "63-day gestation tracking with whelping countdown",
    "AI and frozen-semen breeding documentation",
    "Individual puppy records",
    "Litter management with weights, photos, microchips",
    "Pedigree generation",
    "COI calculation",
    "OFA Sync (Orthopedic Foundation for Animals)",
    "CHIC Readiness Widget",
    "Volhard Puppy Aptitude Test scoring",
    "Gun Dog Aptitude Test scoring",
    "Working-dog role suitability analysis",
    "Rearing protocols (ENS, ESI, Rule of 7s)",
    "Scout AI document extraction (genetics PDFs, vet invoices)",
    "Waitlist management",
    "Deposit and contract tracking",
    "Buyer portal",
    "Built-in marketplace presence",
    "Mobile-first design (iOS, Android, web)",
    "Multi-species support (9 species: dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, cattle)"
  ],
  "offers": {
    "@type": "Offer",
    "name": "14-day free trial",
    "priceCurrency": "USD",
    "description": "14-day free trial of the BreederHQ platform. See pricing page for paid tier details."
  }
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Best Breeder Software 2026: Dog, Cat & Horse Tools Compared"
  description="Honest, side-by-side comparison of 9 breeder software tools: waitlists, deposits, buyer portals and pricing on one page. Try BreederHQ free for 14 days."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <!-- Page-scoped JSON-LD: Article + ItemList + SoftwareApplication (page-specific)
       FAQPage schema is emitted automatically by BaseLayout from the `faqs` prop above. -->
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(itemListSchema)} />
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(softwareSchema)} />

  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:absolute focus:top-4 focus:left-4 focus:z-50 focus:px-4 focus:py-2 focus:bg-white focus:text-black focus:shadow-lg focus:rounded">
    Skip to content
  </a>

  <main id="main-content">
  <nav class="breadcrumb py-4 px-4 bg-gray-50" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 max-w-4xl mx-auto text-sm">
      <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Home</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">тА║</li>
      <li><a href="/compare" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Compare</a></li>
      <li class="text-gray-400">тА║</li>
      <li aria-current="page" class="text-gray-600">Best Dog Breeding Software</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="py-20 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Best Dog Breeding Software 2026: Puppy Waitlist, Deposits, and Buyer Portal Compared</h1>

      <!-- Quick answer block: optimized for AI extraction (40-60 word self-contained answer). -->
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-5 mb-6 rounded">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed">
          <strong>Quick answer:</strong> For a working dog breeding program in 2026, BreederHQ is the most complete option тАФ nine species in one account, integrated public marketplace, OFA Sync, multi-point progesterone tracking, waitlists, deposits, contracts, and a buyer portal, with a 14-day free trial starting at $29/month.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Last updated: June 26, 2026 &middot; Published: May 16, 2026</p>

      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Dog breeder software reviews for the nine tools real breeders shortlist in 2026 тАФ compared on what matters operationally: puppy waitlist software, deposit tracking, contracts, buyer portal, and marketplace presence. Honest trade-offs, no star ratings, no affiliate spin.</p>

      <aside class="tldr-box bg-gray-100 border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] p-6 my-8 rounded" role="complementary" aria-label="Page summary">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">TL;DR: the verdict by program size</h2>
        <ul class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Working program (2+ breeding girls, active waitlist, real contracts):</strong> <a href="#breederhq" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">BreederHQ</a>. Nine species in one account, 14-day free trial, integrated public marketplace, OFA Sync, multi-point progesterone, buyer portal. Built around the working program.</li>
          <li><strong>Single-species dog or cat program that wants records-plus-buyers at one flat price:</strong> <a href="#breederbuddy" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">BreederBuddy</a> at $29.99/mo or $300/year, with a 30-day free trial. Clean interface, no public marketplace, dog or cat only.</li>
          <li><strong>Multi-species records at the lowest entry price:</strong> <a href="#breeder-cloud-pro" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">Breeder Cloud Pro</a> from $6.99/mo with a 30-day trial. Mature, established, includes a "Find a Breeder" directory.</li>
          <li><strong>Breeder who wants a website plus pedigree and genetics on a free or low-cost tier:</strong> <a href="#breed-ledger" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">Breed Ledger</a>. Free to start, then $29/mo or $49/mo. Website builder, cross-breeder pedigrees, species-aware genetics, waitlists, and a buyer-facing directory. Web-based, no native mobile app.</li>
          <li><strong>Hobby breeder upgrading from a notebook:</strong> <a href="#breedera" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">Breedera</a>. Phone-first heat and litter tracker. You will outgrow it once deposits and contracts enter the picture.</li>
          <li><strong>Pedigree-driven club or registry work:</strong> <a href="#zooeasy" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">ZooEasy</a>, <a href="#kintraks" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">Kintraks</a>, or <a href="#pedfast" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">PedFast</a> depending on whether you need a multi-species database, mature records, or pedigree printing.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
          Below: the pricing comparison most other "best of" lists won&apos;t put on one page, the operational workflow matrix, and the honest case for each tool, including where BreederHQ is not the answer.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3">
          <strong>Run multiple species?</strong> See <a href="/breeder-management-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">breeder management software</a> for the species-neutral version of this page.
          <strong class="ml-2">Just need a CRM?</strong> See <a href="/breeder-crm" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline font-semibold">breeder CRM</a> for the inquiry тЖТ waitlist тЖТ deposit тЖТ contract тЖТ buyer-portal pipeline on its own.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <!-- Workflow visual: pill strip (visual content, not schema) -->
      <div class="my-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Puppy waitlist software, deposit tracking, and the rest of the modern breeding workflow</h2>
        <ol class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-2 gap-y-3" aria-label="Stages of a modern dog breeding program">
          {workflowStages.map((stage, i) => (
            <>
              <li class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 rounded-full border-2 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] bg-white text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 whitespace-nowrap shadow-sm">
                {stage}
              </li>
              {i < workflowStages.length - 1 && (
                <li aria-hidden="true" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] font-bold text-lg">тЖТ</li>
              )}
            </>
          ))}
        </ol>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-700">
          <strong>Most breeder software handles one or two of these workflows.</strong> Operational breeders need all of them connected.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-600 italic mt-4">
          If you have looked at "ultimate dog breeding software" lists elsewhere, this is the version that actually shows what each tool does тАФ and does not do тАФ across the puppy waitlist, deposit, contract, and buyer-portal stages.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-8">
        Dog breeding is operational work. Between heat cycles, progesterone tests, whelping nights, puppy applications, deposits, contracts, vet records, and the steady drip of buyer questions, the software you choose either makes that easier or quietly makes it harder.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
        The hard part is that the category is fragmented. Some tools are pedigree databases dressed up with a "breeder" label. Some are old kennel record systems. Some are buyer-facing marketplaces that do not run your program at all. They are not interchangeable, and picking the wrong type costs you months of data entry before you realize it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
        This page compares the tools real dog breeders shortlist in 2026, explains what each is actually good for, and is honest about where each one falls short for an operational program.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick comparison table -->
  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Side-by-side: pricing, species support, and what you actually get</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
        This is the table most "best of" pages won&apos;t put on one screen. Pricing in the column below is each vendor&apos;s publicly listed entry-level price as of June 2026. Species column is what the vendor publicly markets as supported. "Public marketplace" means a buyer-facing public listing site or directory operated by the vendor where prospective buyers search for breeders. Verify everything with a trial.
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 text-left">
            <tr>
              <th scope="col" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Software</th>
              <th scope="col" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Entry price</th>
              <th scope="col" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Free trial</th>
              <th scope="col" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Species</th>
              <th scope="col" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Buyer portal</th>
              <th scope="col" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Public marketplace</th>
              <th scope="col" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">Mobile</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr class="bg-[hsl(24,95%,97%)]">
              <th scope="row" class="px-3 py-3 font-bold text-left">BreederHQ</th>
              <td class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold">See pricing page</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">14 days</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">9 (dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, cattle)</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">Yes</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">Yes (marketplace.breederhq.com)</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">iOS / Android</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold text-left">BreederBuddy</th>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">$29.99/mo or $300/year</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">30 days, no CC</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">2 (dog or cat, one per account)</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">Yes</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">No (optional website add-on)</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">Responsive web</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Breeder Cloud Pro</th>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">$6.99/mo (Standard) / $13.99/mo (Pro)</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">30 days</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">7 (dog, cat, horse, goat, rabbit, sheep, small animals)</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">Yes (pet portal)</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">Directory ("Find a Breeder")</td>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">Responsive web</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row" class="px-3 py-3 font-semibold text-left">Dog Breeder Pro</th>
              <td class="px-3 py-3">$8.49/mo (Standard) / $14.99/mo (Premium)</td>
